\emph{Measuring inequality or concentration} \\
To be able to make qualifying statements about a distribution or to compare different distributions, the concept of inequality turned out to be the most appropriate and thus the most commonly used dimension. See \citet{Allison 1978 FEHLT}, \citet{engelhardt_modelle_2000}, \citet{cowell_chapter_2000} and \citet{hao_assessing_2010}.
